Of course, what was meant at that
time was to establish dharma above all,

00:00:07.567 --> 00:00:10.300
was not to give realisation, but establish dharma

00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:14.345
by expressing human values

00:00:15.309 --> 00:00:17.980
in the perspective of the spiritual absolute,

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:24.500
so that should every human behaviour
should be kept in check by the spiritual finality.

00:00:24.701 --> 00:00:28.300
Now, Saint Dnyaneshwar is an
absolutely extraordinary person.

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:31.940
He died at the age of about 21 years old,

00:00:32.140 --> 00:00:39.140
and after having left behind him a
book which is called JnÄneshvari,

00:00:39.340 --> 00:00:44.106
who is basically a commentary
of the Bhagavad Gita in Sanskrit.

00:00:44.442 --> 00:00:48.180
He - I want to go quickly
through the family story,

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:51.811
but again, they were really
treated as outcasts because

00:00:52.011 --> 00:00:56.860
his father had left his wife to take to Sanyaza,

00:00:57.060 --> 00:01:00.259
and his guru sent him back to married life.

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:03.555
So after that, the Brahmins didn't want at all

00:01:03.755 --> 00:01:08.260
to have anything to do with a Brahmin
who had gone back to family life.

00:01:08.460 --> 00:01:11.419
So they were treated like
dirt by all the Brahmins,

00:01:11.620 --> 00:01:15.381
but they were, I don't know,
three brothers and two sisters,

00:01:15.581 --> 00:01:22.340
and they were all very highly realised souls, and actually
his brother got his initiation and gave it to him.

00:01:22.570 --> 00:01:27.595
Now, there are many miracles
in the life of Dnyaneshwar,

00:01:27.795 --> 00:01:30.187
which are famous. For instance,

00:01:30.387 --> 00:01:37.434
while he was arguing with a couple of learned
pendants saying that God is everywhere and in everything,

00:01:37.635 --> 00:01:43.480
then they made a fool out of him, and they said, well, if God is everything and if the Vedas are everything, can you make this cow say the Vedas?

00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:48.299
And he went to the cow, and buffalo, I
don't know, started reciting the Vedas.

00:01:48.499 --> 00:01:52.827
And so, you know, I mean, he was rather good, huh.

00:01:53.858 --> 00:01:58.460
We can't do that yet.
Try on any buffalo, it won't work.

00:01:58.973 --> 00:02:03.500
So another example, which is very sweet,

00:02:03.700 --> 00:02:09.780
there was one of these big ascetic, which came down to
their place because they started being famous, of course.

00:02:09.980 --> 00:02:13.220
And he came on the back
of a tiger trying to show off.

00:02:13.420 --> 00:02:18.860
And Dnyaneshwar was sitting on a rock, like
on a little wall with his brothers and sisters,

00:02:19.060 --> 00:02:23.980
and he said, oh, here's the great saint. I
don't know what he who is coming to visit us.

00:02:24.180 --> 00:02:25.757
Let's just pay our homage to the saint.

00:02:25.957 --> 00:02:31.380
And then the rock flew and they
all flew on the rock to meet the saint.

00:02:31.580 --> 00:02:37.332
And then when the saint on his poor tiger looked at
this, he was completely, you know, ruled over, I mean.

00:02:37.533 --> 00:02:42.380
He realised it was rather smarter to
move on a on a wall than on a tiger.

00:02:42.580 --> 00:02:44.777
Then he prostrated himself before Dnyaneshwar.

00:02:44.977 --> 00:02:47.172
And Shri Mataji, when she commented on this,

00:02:47.373 --> 00:02:51.460
she said, this is Shri Hanumana who
is playing this trick. He carried the wall

00:02:51.660 --> 00:02:53.780
because Shri Hanumana
is the master of the siddhis.

00:02:53.980 --> 00:02:56.898
That is, he's the master of
all the magic magical powers,

00:02:57.099 --> 00:03:02.380
as you know, as he brought back the
whole mountain to cure Lakshmana.

00:03:03.007 --> 00:03:09.220
Now, just after this few
biographic notes, he died here.

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:13.453
This is the place of the office, what we call
Maha-samadhi, when he departed his body,

00:03:13.653 --> 00:03:17.020
or Chaitanya Samadhi, because he left in meditation.

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:21.839
He was deep into Nirikalpa Samadhi.
And in that consciousness, he left his body.

00:03:22.040 --> 00:03:28.180
So it's not when we, like when we die, we are kind
of thrown out of our body by Yama, the God of death,

00:03:28.380 --> 00:03:34.110
but these people, they just leave
the human kosha, the envelope.

00:03:34.311 --> 00:03:38.875
Now, just one thing you need
to know about his message.

00:03:39.075 --> 00:03:43.460
